@dongjoon-hyun Thanks for the reply. I should have be more specific for what I'd like to point out: I agree that it's great to support as many versions as possible. Also, the maintenance cost is tiny as you mentioned.
However, the guide (README.md) will have a long list if we keep all the supported versions. We can avoid this just by showing in a different way (e.g., adding "Supported versions" column and having "0.24-0.27" in Mesos row)
This is a minor improvement and can be handled in a separate PR though. I think we can merge this PR as it is for now :)

@afchung, @markusweimer
Please take a look.
Ran tests on Yarn cluster and they passed.

Hi, I think we need to upgrade the script. The problem comes here, `lang\cs\Org.Apache.REEF.Examples\ConfigFiles\evaluator.conf`.
As you see, the version and public key is hard-coded.

```
Obj^A^B^Vavro.schema~~~
  "Bindings": [
    {
      "key": "Org.Apache.REEF.Common.Tasks.ITask, Org.Apache.REEF.Common, Version=0.14.0.0, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=c27bf5b2e9a7ddb9",
      "value": "Org.Apache.REEF.Examples.HelloREEF.HelloTask, Org.Apache.REEF.Examples.HelloREEF, Version=0.14.0.0, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=c27bf5b2e9a7ddb9"
    },
    {
      "key": "Org.Apache.REEF.Common.Tasks.TaskConfigurationOptions+Identifier, Org.Apache.REEF.Common, Version=0.14.0.0, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=c27bf5b2e9a7ddb9",
      "value": "HelloTask"
    }
  ]
} ^Aorg.apache.reef.runtime.common.evaluator.parameters.RootContextConfiguration ^D{
  "language": "Cs",
  "Bindings": [
    {
      "key": "Org.Apache.REEF.Driver.Context.ContextConfigurationOptions+ContextIdentifier, Org.Apache.REEF.Driver, Version=0.14.0.0, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=c27bf5b2e9a7ddb9",
      "value": "RootContext_Node-2-1447450298921"
    }
  ]
}
```
